@Node CharFuncs
@Title "Character Type Macros and Functions"
Function	   Portability	 Description

@{" isalnum        " Link isalnum()}   ANSI          check if a character is alphanumeric
@{" isalpha        " Link isalpha()}   ANSI          check if a character is alphabetic
@{" isascii        " Link isascii()}   SAS/C         check if a character is an ASCII character
@{" iscntrl        " Link iscntrl()}   ANSI          check if a character is a control character
@{" iscsym         " Link iscsym()}   SAS/C         check if a character is a C symbol character
@{" iscsymf        " Link iscsymf()}   SAS/C         check if a character is a C symbol lead character
@{" isdigit        " Link isdigit()}   ANSI          check if a character is a decimal digit (0-9)
@{" isgraph        " Link isgraph()}   ANSI          check if a character is a graphic character
@{" islower        " Link islower()}   ANSI          check if a character is lowercase
@{" isprint        " Link isprint()}   ANSI          check if a character is printable
@{" ispunct        " Link ispunct()}   ANSI          check if a character is a punctuation character
@{" isspace        " Link isspace()}   ANSI          check if a character is a space
@{" isupper        " Link isupper()}   ANSI          check if a character is uppercase
@{" isxdigit       " Link isxdigit()}   ANSI          check if a character is a hex character (0-9, A-F, a-f)
@{" toascii        " Link toascii()}   SAS/C         convert a character to an ASCII character
@{" tolower        " Link tolower()}   ANSI          convert a character to lowercase
@{" toupper        " Link toupper()}   ANSI          convert a character to uppercase
@EndNode

@Node StringFuncs
@Title "String Functions"
See also "Memory Manipulation Functions," later in this section.

Function	   Portability	 Description

@{" astcsma        " Link astcsma()}   AmigaDOS      AmigaDOS string pattern match (anchored)
@{" scdir          " Link scdir()}   OLD           Return the name of the next file matching pattern
@{" stcpm          " Link stcpm()}   SAS/C         unanchored pattern match
@{" stcpma         " Link stcpma()}   SAS/C         anchored pattern match
@{" stcsma         " Link stcsma()}   AmigaDOS      UNIX string pattern match (anchored)
@{" stccpy         " Link stccpy()}   UNIX          copy one string to another
@{" stpcpy         " Link stpcpy()}   SAS/C         copy one string to another
@{" strcpy         " Link strcpy()}   ANSI          copy one string to another
@{" strncpy        " Link strncpy()}   ANSI          copy a string, length limited
@{" stcis          " Link stcis()}   SAS/C         count the number of string characters in the set
@{" stcisn         " Link stcisn()}   SAS/C         count the number of string characters not in the set
@{" strcspn        " Link strcspn()}   ANSI          count the number of string characters not in the set
@{" stclen         " Link stclen()}   OLD           measure the length of a string
@{" strlen         " Link strlen()}   ANSI          measure the length of a string
@{" strspn         " Link strspn()}   ANSI          count longest span of characters in the set
@{" stpbrk         " Link stpbrk()}   OLD           find a break character in a string
@{" stpchr         " Link stpchr()}   OLD           find a character in a string
