@Node stclen()
stclen-Measure the length of a string

Synopsis

	#include <string.h>

	length = stclen(s);

	size_t length;	 /* number of bytes in s (before null) */
	const char *s;

Description

	This function, which is equivalent to the ANSI Standard function
	@{" strlen " Link strlen()},  returns the number of bytes in the string s before the
	NULL terminator byte.

	This function is implemented as a macro and is provided only for
	compatibility with previous releases.

	This function is not available if the @{" _STRICT_ANSI " Link _STRICT_ANSI} flag has been
	defined.

Portability

	@{" OLD " Link "Glossary - OLD"}

Returns

	The length equals the number of bytes in the string before the
	NULL byte.

